# T-1705 · Demo build flag, applied via Vite's mode system: `vite build --mode demo`
# loads this file and bakes VITE_SQ_DEMO into the bundle (read by src/demo.ts).
# This replaces the old inline `VITE_SQ_DEMO=1 vite build` script, which was
# POSIX-only syntax — npm runs package.json scripts through cmd.exe on Windows,
# where inline env assignments do not parse (the T-1705 windows-latest CI failure).
# A mode file is cross-platform and dependency-free (no cross-env).
VITE_SQ_DEMO=1
